The paper proposes a method for discovering artifact lifecycle models, which is a topic related to software engineering (cs.SE). The method involves analyzing business processes, which often involve large amounts of data and require efficient data management techniques, making it relevant to database research (cs.DB). The paper also mentions the reuse of existing process discovery and analysis methods, which can be seen as a form of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed methods are implemented as software plug-ins, which involves programming and machine learning techniques, making it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the use of a generic open-source framework for implementing process mining tools, which can be seen as a topic related to cybersecurity (cs.CY).
